  <li id="comment-33786" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Kai</cite></div>
      <a href="index.html?p=419#comment-33786"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2012-03-27T17:00:52-04:00">Tuesday, March 27, 2012 at 5:00 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I&#39;ve made the following mistake with Kim Boyce&#39;s recipes before, and I would like to warn you all away from doing the same &#8211; when the woman says &#8220;kosher salt,&#8221; she MEANS kosher salt. I unthinkingly used sea salt for this recipe and the salted peanut butter cookies Molly&#39;s posted previously, and in both cases they were inedible. Be warned, people! Go kosher or go home!</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='index.html?p=419#comment-33786' data-commentid="33786" data-postid="419" data-belowelement="comment-33786" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Kai" aria-label='Reply to Kai'>Reply</a>    </div>
