    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Man these bars look awesome. I love food that crumbles.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='index.html?p=419#comment-33818' data-commentid="33818" data-postid="419" data-belowelement="comment-33818" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Elizabeth" aria-label='Reply to Elizabeth'>Reply</a>    </div>
  </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-33908" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/01036627416016369648" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Elizabeth</a></cite></div>
      <a href="index.html?p=419#comment-33908"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2012-06-10T00:26:44-04:00">Sunday, June 10, 2012 at 12:26 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Man these bars look awesome. I love food that crumbles.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='index.html?p=419#comment-33908' data-commentid="33908" data-postid="419" data-belowelement="comment-33908" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Elizabeth" aria-label='Reply to Elizabeth'>Reply</a>    </div>
  </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-33819" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="http://www.rawhoney.ca" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Mike</a></cite></div>
      <a href="index.html?p=419#comment-33819"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2012-10-02T18:09:56-04:00">Tuesday, October 2, 2012 at 6:09 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>A lot of people take time of from work when they are pregnant. The best thing you can do to increase your productivity is to take care of yourself. When it comes to writing or any type of work your going to have bad days. The worse thing you can do is be hard on yourself because that is not going to help you at all. Taking a break and making rye crumble bars may be the best thing for you. This mental break could just be what the doctor ordered. Let your creativity flow and don&#39;t let any emotional stress ruin that flow.  </p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='index.html?p=419#comment-33819' data-commentid="33819" data-postid="419" data-belowelement="comment-33819" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Mike" aria-label='Reply to Mike'>Reply</a>    </div>
  </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-33909" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="http://www.rawhoney.ca" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Mike</a></cite></div>
      <a href="index.html?p=419#comment-33909"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2012-10-02T18:09:56-04:00">Tuesday, October 2, 2012 at 6:09 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>A lot of people take time of from work when they are pregnant. The best thing you can do to increase your productivity is to take care of yourself. When it comes to writing or any type of work your going to have bad days. The worse thing you can do is be hard on yourself because that is not going to help you at all. Taking a break and making rye crumble bars may be the best thing for you. This mental break could just be what the doctor ordered. Let your creativity flow and don&#39;t let any emotional stress ruin that flow.  </p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='index.html?p=419#comment-33909' data-commentid="33909" data-postid="419" data-belowelement="comment-33909" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Mike" aria-label='Reply to Mike'>Reply</a>    </div>
  </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-66994" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">oaklandpat</cite></div>
      <a href="index.html?p=419#comment-66994"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2017-09-18T23:03:42-04:00">Monday, September 18, 2017 at 11:03 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>So late to the party, but hoping someone can set me straight on pan size.  I want to make these in a square or rectangular pan so that I can cut them into tidy little squares.  I&#8217;m wondering what size would be best to substitute for the 9&#8243; springform.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='index.html?p=419#comment-66994' data-commentid="66994" data-postid="419" data-belowelement="comment-66994" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to oaklandpat" aria-label='Reply to oaklandpat'>Reply</a>    </div>
  <ol class="children">
  <li id="comment-67048" class="comment byuser comment-author-molly bypostauthor odd alt depth-2">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="http://orangette.net" class="url" rel="ugc">Molly</a></cite></div>
      <a href="index.html?p=419#comment-67048"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2017-09-21T18:37:18-04:00">Thursday, September 21, 2017 at 6:37 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I imagine you could get away with using a 9&#8243; square pan. Try it! When in doubt, I generally lean on conversation charts like <a href="http://dish.allrecipes.com/cake-pan-size-conversions/" rel="nofollow">this one</a>.</p>
    </div>

